==========================================================
 HOW TO READ THIS
==========================================================
 A usable control needs: n >= 8, ONE locality (or few), a tight date
 span, and one platform. Anything with sites >= 3 or span >= 800 is a
 BIN and is disqualified -- by this project's own Recommendation 2.

 If nothing usable turns up for Iran_GanjDareh, that hole is PERMANENT
 and Paper B must state that its diagnostic cannot screen the source
 that contributes most to the target. It already half-says this.

 Nothing is concluded here. Read the counts.
